stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> IDLE

    IDLE --> LIFECYCLE_S: page read/write/recovery
    IDLE --> LIFECYCLE_X: drop/truncate/discard

    LIFECYCLE_S --> HANDLE_LOCKED: validate file handle
    HANDLE_LOCKED --> SIZE_CHECKED: read stable file size
    SIZE_CHECKED --> PAGE_RANGE_LOCKED: optional page range lock
    PAGE_RANGE_LOCKED --> IO_IN_PROGRESS: positional read/write
    IO_IN_PROGRESS --> FSYNC_LIMITED: fsync requested
    IO_IN_PROGRESS --> RELEASED: read/write done
    FSYNC_LIMITED --> RELEASED: fsync done

    LIFECYCLE_S --> EXTENDING: acquire FileSizeLock X
    EXTENDING --> SIZE_PUBLISHED: zero fill new range
    SIZE_PUBLISHED --> RELEASED: publish currentSizeInPages

    LIFECYCLE_X --> DRAINING_IO: block new IO and wait S holders
    DRAINING_IO --> FILE_MUTATION: close/truncate/drop
    FILE_MUTATION --> RELEASED: publish space version

    RELEASED --> IDLE
    IDLE --> [*]

    note right of LIFECYCLE_S
        Does not enter transaction Wait-For Graph.
        Timeout or IO error is handled by Disk Manager.
    end note

    note right of LIFECYCLE_X
        DDL or cleanup owns lifecycle X latch.
        Buffer Pool must stop returning ordinary page handles.
    end note

